This is the step by step guide for Installing and using Git and github on Ubunutu Linux: A biginner's guide
1. Installing Git for linux
sudo apt-get install git

2. Configuring github

git config --global user.name "username"
git config --global user.email "email_id"

3. create a local repository

git init Mytest

Intialized empty Git repository in /root/Mytest/.git/

cd Mytest

4. nano README

This is a gir repo


5. Adding repository files to an index
create a file by the name sample.c by running command nano sample.c
#include <stdio.h>
int main ()
{
printf("helo world");

return 0;
}
now you have two files README and sample.c



git add READNE
git add sample.c


6. commiting changes made to the index

git commit -m "how to install and use git and github"

7. create the new reposity on the github.com by clicling on the plus sign

git remote add origin https://github.com/qirfan/Mytest.git

git push origin master



